1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
 Hi. I have a question for you all. Who here, by show of hands please, who here watches Netflix?

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
 Okay great. So my husband and I love a good show and as new parents we're not really able to watch as we used to.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:28,000
 But when we get those little moments and we get the chance to just sit down and unwind, we really love a good British limited series.

4
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:39,000
 Yeah, right. They're usually really short and they're jam-packed, cliffhangers, amazing storylines and they sort of leave you at the edge of your seat like,

5
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:50,000
 "What's going to happen next? What's going to happen to this person?" But at the end of the series there's always a bit of a sigh and that's just it. It's over.

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 And now funnily enough there's a little series or a two-parter in the Bible and we've been looking at part one of it for the last few weeks.

7
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:07,000
 It's written by Luke. Both the Book of Luke and Acts are part of the same series and they're both about Jesus.

8
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:18,000
 And trust me, it's more than your average Netflix show. Part one, the Book of Luke, as you may have noticed, speaks about the anticipation of the coming Christ,

9
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:24,000
 his birth, his miracles, his death and his resurrection. And it's all from eyewitness accounts.

10
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:32,000
 Part two in the Book of Acts is what happens after Jesus ascends into heaven, the Holy Spirit overtakes,

11
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:39,000
 and how the Word of God, the Gospel, spreads from Jerusalem to the rest of the world.

12
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 And trust me, if you've read Acts, you know there's no shortage of extraordinary miracles and a show of the power of God.

13
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:57,000
 Now, I mentioned Netflix earlier because there's often the temptation to look at the Bible the same way we look at a film or a series.

14
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:08,000
 It's entertaining whilst we're watching it, like in the moment, and maybe you talk about it a little bit afterwards, but it fades very, very quickly.

15
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:15,000
 It's like it fades into the box of memories of many, many other films that you've seen and that you've watched.

16
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:21,000
 So as we continue to look through Luke today, I want to challenge us not to do the same thing.

17
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:33,000
 Let's not look at the Word of God like we do a film or a show on Netflix, where we're engaged in the moment and then we forget all about it as soon as we finish.

18
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:42,000
 Where we don't apply what we've read into our own lives and we make the mistake of looking at the Bible as some sort of fictional story.

19
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
 The Word of God is true. The Word of God is life changing.

20
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:55,000
 And it should be read with the expectation that every time we open it, God has something to say and he wants to meet with us.

21
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:59,000
 So have this in mind as we look at the text today.

22
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:04,000
 The Word of God is true. The Word of God changes lives.

23
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:09,000
 It always, always, always, always brings freedom and it goes far beyond us.

24
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:13,000
 It never returns to him void.

25
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:21,000
 Last week, Chapman took us through Mary's song and today we're going to take a look at Zechariah's song.

26
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:27,000
 I'm going to read a little bit before that so we get a better picture of what has happened and what brings him to actually sing.

27
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 It's quite a long one, but I do think it's important to read the whole thing so then we can dive into it a little bit deeper.

28
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:43,000
 So it's in Luke 1, verse 57 to 80.

29
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:50,000
 And it reads, "When it was time for Elizabeth to have her baby, she gave birth to a son.

30
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:56,000
 Her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had shown her great mercy and they shared her joy.

31
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 On the eighth day, they came to circumcise the child and they were going to name him after his father, Zechariah.

32
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
 But his mother spoke up and said, 'No, he is to be called John.'

33
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:13,000
 They said to her, 'There is no one among your relatives who has that name.'

34
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:19,000
 Then they made signs to his father to find out what he would like to name the child.

35
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:27,000
 He asked for a writing tablet and to everyone's astonishment, he wrote, 'His name is John.'

36
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:33,000
 Immediately, his mouth was opened and his tongue set free and he began to speak, praising God.

37
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:41,000
 All the neighbors were filled with awe and throughout the hill country and Judea, people were talking about all these things.

38
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:47,000
 Everyone who had heard this wondered about it, asking, 'What then is this child going to be?'

39
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:51,000
 For the Lord's hand was with him."

40
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,000
 Verse 67, now we're getting into the song.

41
00:04:54,000 --> 00:05:02,000
 "His father, Zechariah, was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied, 'Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israel,

42
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
 for he has come to his people and redeemed them.

43
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:11,000
 He has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David,

44
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:18,000
 as he said through his holy prophets long ago, 'Salvation from our enemies and from the hand of all who hate us,

45
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:23,000
 to show mercy to our ancestors and to remember his holy covenant,

46
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,000
 the oath he swore to our father Abraham to rescue us from the hand of our enemies

47
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 and to enable us to serve him without fear in holiness and righteousness before him all our days.

48
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,000
 And you, my child, will be called a prophet of the Most High,

49
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:44,000
 for you will go before the Lord to prepare the way for him,

50
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:49,000
 to give his people the knowledge of salvation through the forgiveness of their sins,

51
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:55,000
 because of the tender mercy of our God by which the rising sun will come to us from heaven,

52
00:05:55,000 --> 00:06:00,000
 to shine on those living in darkness and in the shadow of death,

53
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,000
 to guide our feet into the path of peace.'

54
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
 And the child grew and became strong in spirit,

55
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:13,000
 and he lived in the wilderness until he appeared publicly to Israel. Amen."

56
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:18,000
 So, from this verses, it's really clear to see that God is at work.

57
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:22,000
 A few weeks ago, we saw Mary's encounter with the angel,

58
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 we also saw Zechariah's, all within the same time period, not centuries apart.

59
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
 And we also saw how they both responded.

60
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:36,000
 Mary welcomed the word of the Lord, "I am your servant,"

61
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:41,000
 while Zechariah doubted, "How can I be sure of this?"

62
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:45,000
 His doubt actually echoes another story in the Old Testament.

63
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:50,000
 It's quite similar to this one in terms of barrenness and waiting on the Lord.

64
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:54,000
 We read in Genesis 18 that Sarah had a similar reaction

65
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,000
 when she heard that she would have a child in her old age.

66
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:02,000
 In fact, she thought it was so ridiculous that she laughed.

67
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:07,000
 Now, can you imagine your grandma, actually your great grandma,

68
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 telling you she's pregnant, she's about to have a baby?

69
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:16,000
 You would probably laugh and think it was a joke too.

70
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:22,000
 But the Lord says to Abraham in verse 14, "Is anything too hard for the Lord?"

71
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:29,000
 Sarah was past childbearing age, and it really didn't seem like a feasible task.

72
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:35,000
 But this was a reminder that if God says it, he can and he will do it.

73
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:41,000
 Nothing is impossible for God, which is the same message that we get here in Luke

74
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
 and in many other parts of the Bible.

75
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:52,000
 So this was said by the angel to Elizabeth, "For no word from God will ever fail."

76
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:57,000
 Even Elizabeth, your relative, is going to have a child in her old age,

77
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:02,000
 and she who was said to be unable to conceive is in her sixth month.

78
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:08,000
 I'll say it again, "For no word from God will ever fail."

79
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,000
 And in the book of Isaiah, this is from the Lord himself.

80
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
 "So is my word that goes out from my mouth.

81
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
 It will not return to me empty, but will accomplish what I desire

82
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:23,000
 and achieve the purpose for which I have sent it."

83
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:27,000
 Once he has spoken, we can be sure that he will fulfill it,

84
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:32,000
 and ultimately, everything is fulfilled in the person of Jesus.

85
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:37,000
 Now, a few weeks back, we saw how Zechariah's mouth was actually muted.

86
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:41,000
 He doubted the word of the Lord that was spoken to him by the angel,

87
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:46,000
 and then he was unable to speak until after his son was born.

88
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:55,000
 But even in his silence, he was able to declare that which God had already spoken.

89
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:59,000
 As baby John was getting circumcised, eight days after his birth,

90
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:04,000
 he was asked what the child's name was, and instead of what was common practice,

91
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:09,000
 naming the child after a relative, he broke the mold and did something very different.

92
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:13,000
 He chose in that moment to walk in obedience

93
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:17,000
 and follow the instructions that were given to him by the angel.

94
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 And though he doubted at the beginning, he did, he also saw God's word come to pass.

95
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,000
 He saw that, indeed, Elizabeth became pregnant.

96
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
 He saw that she had given birth to their son,

97
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:36,000
 and that their old age meant nothing because God had said it, and the miracle was done.

98
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:41,000
 Just as it was done for Abraham centuries before, God was doing it again.

99
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 And now all eyes were on Zechariah.

100
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,000
 What are you going to name this boy?

101
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 And Zechariah decided to follow what the Lord had said.

102
00:09:54,000 --> 00:10:00,000
 And as soon as he wrote down his name as John, it says,

103
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
 "Immediately his mouth was opened and his tongue set free,

104
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:08,000
 and he began to speak, praising God."

105
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 Now, declaring the word of the Lord brings freedom.

106
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:19,000
 In Zechariah's case, it was freedom of his tongue and having the ability to speak again.

107
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:24,000
 We also see God's word bringing freedom to the children of Israel in the book of Exodus.

108
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 The Israelites were slaves in Egypt and longed for their freedom.

109
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:33,000
 And as Moses continually spoke to Pharaoh, declaring God's words,

110
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:37,000
 "Let my people go so they may worship me,"

111
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
 the power of God broke through and the Israelites were set free.

112
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:46,000
 When we speak God's word, his truth, into situations, there is always freedom,

113
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:51,000
 whether it be physical freedom, spiritual, or freedom from sin.

114
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:56,000
 Now, if you're an old man, you've got no children,

115
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:59,000
 you've been praying and waiting for decades,

116
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 probably going to the temple on a regular basis and just waiting on God.

117
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:12,000
 We know that being childless was looked down upon because we see Elizabeth's words in verse 25.

118
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:18,000
 "He has shown me favor and taken away my disgrace among the people."

119
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,000
 And it finally happens.

120
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,000
 The Lord does this great thing.

121
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 And after months of not being able to speak, what would be the first words out of your mouth?

122
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:34,000
 I know for me, I might be a little bit sour at first.

123
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 Not being able to speak for all that time throughout the pregnancy of our first child,

124
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:44,000
 there must have been so many moments that he wanted to just exclaim,

125
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:48,000
 you know, feeling that first kick, all sorts of things.

126
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:54,000
 Or maybe just so excited about this miracle that I'd be so obsessed with my baby,

127
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 which is often the case, and the prayers and the praise to God comes later.

128
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:02,000
 But Zechariah doesn't speak about John.

129
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:07,000
 He doesn't even speak about his wife, but immediately praises God.

130
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 And what follows is incredible.

131
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:17,000
 His father, Zechariah, was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied.

132
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:21,000
 And to prophesy is to speak about things that are to come.

133
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:26,000
 So events that haven't happened, but certainly will in the future.

134
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
 It's not fortune telling.

135
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,000
 It's none of this weird new age stuff that you hear about today.

136
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
 No tarot cards, no odd practices.

137
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,000
 It's nothing to do with our own strength.

138
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,000
 It's always prophecies that come from God are always true,

139
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:45,000
 and they always happen at their appointed time.

140
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 And at this time, the Holy Spirit had not yet fallen on all men.

141
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:55,000
 So there are moments throughout the Old Testament where you see people are overpowered,

142
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:59,000
 empowered by the Holy Spirit to do something or to speak.

143
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 But we need to be aware that it isn't like what we experience today,

144
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:10,000
 where we can lay hands on each other and ask for a filling of the Holy Spirit.

145
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
 This was something that came much later.

146
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 And there's a prophecy in Joel that speaks about these days,

147
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:20,000
 the days that we are actually living in today.

148
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,000
 What a privilege.

149
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:26,000
 So what we read in Luke is actually an anticipation of what is to come.

150
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:31,000
 It's little glimpses of the power of the Holy Spirit.

151
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 The angel said John would be filled with the Holy Spirit even before his birth.

152
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:41,000
 And we see that Elizabeth gets filled with the Holy Spirit in verse 41.

153
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
 And now Zechariah.

154
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:49,000
 We know today that the filling of the Spirit often accompanies a great move of God.

155
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:54,000
 In the book of Acts 2, after the disciples were filled with the Holy Spirit,

156
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:58,000
 they go out healing the sick, speaking in tongues, casting out demons,

157
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 and doing all sorts of things in the power of the Holy Spirit.

158
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:06,000
 And we have the ability to look back on these things.

159
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:14,000
 And as we put our faith in Jesus now, we can also be filled with the same Holy Spirit.

160
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,000
 But here, Zechariah is looking ahead.

161
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:21,000
 He's speaking of things that haven't actually happened.

162
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:27,000
 He's speaking of things he had heard by word of mouth or by reading the scrolls.

163
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 So verses 68 to 65.

164
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,000
 Let's have a little look.

165
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:37,000
 "Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israel, because he has come to his people and redeemed them.

166
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:41,000
 He's raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David,

167
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:45,000
 as he said through his holy prophets of long ago.

168
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
 Salvation from our enemies and from the hand of all who hate us,

169
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 to show mercy to our ancestors and to remember his holy covenant,

170
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 the oath he swore our father Abraham,

171
00:14:55,000 --> 00:15:00,000
 to rescue us from the hand of our enemies and to enable us to serve him without fear,

172
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 in holiness and righteousness before him all our days."

173
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:09,000
 Zechariah is pointing to the coming Christ in this prophecy.

174
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 He's sent to earth to redeem and save mankind, the most important event in our history.

175
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 That through the family of David, a revered king amongst the Israelites,

176
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:27,000
 the ultimate King Jesus would come and fulfill the word of God.

177
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:32,000
 That all the Old Testament prophecies, all the words that God spoke before,

178
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 through the prophets would come to pass.

179
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:40,000
 So in case you missed it, this prophecy is all about Jesus.

180
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,000
 And we know that it is true because all of this has actually happened,

181
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,000
 just as he said it would.

182
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 Everything is about him.

183
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:54,000
 Zechariah realized that his own life, the birth of John, the surrounding events,

184
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
 they were all part of a greater story.

185
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 By praising the Lord, he actively participated in the move of God

186
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:06,000
 and what he was doing at that time.

187
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:11,000
 He didn't look at his own life, nor did he focus on the birth of his son

188
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,000
 or put that at the forefront.

189
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,000
 All of that was secondary.

190
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 He knew that greater things were to come.

191
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 His humility opened him up to seeing that he was not the main character.

192
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 And, surprise, surprise guys, neither are we.

193
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:36,000
 Even in our own lives, our stories are no longer about us.

194
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:42,000
 The minute we become Christians, we often say we've given our lives to Christ.

195
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:48,000
 He becomes the first and the last, and we surrender everything to him.

196
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 We give him the praise.

197
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
 We give him the honor.

198
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:56,000
 Colossians 3 says we do everything as unto the Lord.

199
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 So that's your work life, the way you speak to each other, your family,

200
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:06,000
 what we put in our bodies, everything is for him and about him.

201
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:09,000
 We are no longer the main characters.

202
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 Now, I'm going to take you back to our little Netflix example.

203
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:22,000
 By show of hands, please, have a good look at these four guys.

204
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:28,000
 I'm going to point to one, and I'm going to ask how many people recognize this person.

205
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 So I'm going to start with this guy.

206
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:35,000
 Show of hands, how many of you have ever seen this man?

207
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,000
 Okay.

