 This guy, no one recognized this guy, which is great.

219
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:21,000
 So you recognize these two the most because they are the main characters in their films.

220
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,000
 They're the main actors.

221
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,000
 So the storylines are centered around them, their lives.

222
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 There might be some random love interest in there or something.

223
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 But for the most part, everything is about those guys.

224
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:45,000
 And it's interesting how they manage to keep us interested and invested in this character throughout the whole film.

225
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:49,000
 The other two guys, you ask, never seen them before?

226
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,000
 Nope.

227
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:54,000
 I had never seen them either until I started preparing for this sermon.

228
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:58,000
 And that's because they are actually stunt doubles.

229
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:01,000
 Yeah.

230
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:09,000
 So a stunt double is a trained professional who stands in for an actor to perform dangerous or demanding tasks.

231
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 So obviously, you won't see the actual Daniel Craig jumping out of a helicopter or a building.

232
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 It will be a stunt double.

233
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:25,000
 The two guys from the previous slides were their stunt doubles.

234
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 So those are the people that will be doing all the dangerous things.

235
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
 Yeah.

236
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 So the actor does the majority of the film with no regard for the stunt double.

237
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 All of the easy things, goes about his business.

238
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 But when he or she comes to that scene that requires a bit more strength, that's a bit dangerous, could cause a bit of harm or pain,

239
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 they just step aside, let the stunt double come and do it.

240
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
 And they do it to perfection.

241
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 But they're always in the background.

242
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 No one ever knows there was a stunt double.

243
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 It happens so quickly.

244
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 And there's never a pause in the film that says, "This stunt was performed by a stunt double."

245
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 Never, ever happens.

246
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 And if you don't know much about films or you blink a bit too quickly, you may assume that it was the main actor who did it.

247
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:21,000
 And all of the awards, all of the accolades, go to the main actor.

248
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 There is not an Oscar for stunt doubles.

249
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 Surprise, surprise.

250
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 There should be, right?

251
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,000
 But there isn't.

252
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
 Now, think about your own life for a second.

253
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 How many times have we been the main characters in our own stories and relegated God to our stunt double?

254
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 We call him when times are tough.

255
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:51,000
 He comes in, he does the job, and then we push him to the background.

256
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 No praise, no honor, no recognition.

257
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,000
 It's all about us.

258
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:07,000
 And as I was preparing for this sermon, I actually had to humble myself and repent because I realized that I was doing the exact same thing.

259
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,000
 I was in two minds about doing this sermon.

260
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,000
 And I had like a million questions.

261
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 I've narrowed them down.

262
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,000
 Should I?

263
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,000
 Shouldn't I?

264
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,000
 All eyes on me.

265
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 I may not be able to just fade into the background after doing this.

266
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 I don't particularly like speaking in public.

267
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,000
 What if I say the wrong thing?

268
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,000
 I'm not a pastor.

269
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:34,000
 Should I be preaching?

270
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,000
 Now, let's look at those questions again.

271
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:41,000
 And I've made all of the I's and all of the me's bold.

272
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 So we can all count it together.

273
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

274
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,000
 Eight times.

275
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 And trust me, I had way more questions.

276
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,000
 There's way more I's and me's.

277
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 Loads more.

278
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,000
 So how many times did I talk about myself?

279
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,000
 Eight times.

280
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 How many times did I mention God?

281
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,000
 How many times did I mention his will?

282
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 What he has to say?

283
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:15,000
 I had made preaching and declaring his word all about me.

284
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 And we often go about life in this exact same way.

285
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 We live for ourselves.

286
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:34,000
 We wake up in the morning, it's about our kids, our spouses, our jobs, what we're going to eat, what we're going to wear, what will people think of us, where we need to be, what we need to do.

287
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 We often don't even consider what God has for us each day.

288
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 And we go through the motions, doing life, going through the script, saying our lines, until we get to the crossroad where we need our trusted stunt double.

289
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:58,000
 And in preparing for this sermon, perhaps my mindset should have been this instead.

290
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 What does God want to share with his church?

291
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:09,000
 How will he use me?

292
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 I'm going to read that again.

293
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:16,000
 What does God want to share with his church?

294
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 How will God, how will he use me?

295
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 See, once you change your perspective and you shift your gaze to him, you realize that it isn't about you.

296
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:39,000
 You are not the main character.

297
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,000
 He is.

298
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 And it is about what he wants to do in and through you.

299
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:50,000
 Now, Zachariah had the right idea.

300
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:56,000
 He made God the center and had set his eyes on the things above.

301
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 Luke 1 says he and Elizabeth were righteous in the sight of God, observing his commands blamelessly, and even after doubting, he was obedient and followed the word of the Lord, praising God and looking to him as the most important.

302
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:20,000
 What he had just experienced was an afterthought.

303
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:28,000
 When he looked ahead at what was to come, all of the prophecies of old were about to be seen in his day.

304
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:37,000
 And his son would prepare the way for the Messiah, the Christ, the Redeemer, the horn or the strength of salvation.

305
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:43,000
 He would see scriptures that he had heard as a boy fulfilled.

306
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:49,000
 And only after he speaks about Christ does he mention John, his son.

307
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,000
 Jesus was always first.

308
00:24:52,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 And when we believe in God and we believe in his words and we're obedient to him, we make him the main character.

309
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 Just like Zachariah did. As we build our lives on him, we become, he becomes the center and we become a part of the big story that he is writing.

310
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:28,000
 Let's just take 10 seconds and just have a think about that last part.

311
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:33,000
 As we build our lives on him, he becomes the center.

312
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:52,000
 We become a big a part of the big story that he is writing.

313
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 Can we just call up the worship team?

314
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:03,000
 So I want us to have a think about our own lives.

315
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:08,000
 How do we see Jesus?

316
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:11,000
 Is he the main character?

317
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:14,000
 Are we part of his great story?

318
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:20,000
 Or is he a tiny part of ours, like a stunt double?

319
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:25,000
 So there's this worship song that I absolutely adore.

320
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:28,000
 And it goes like this.

321
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,000
 I'm not going to sing, by the way.

322
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:34,000
 No, I'm not going to break into song.

323
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,000
 It seemed like a moment, right?

324
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,000
 No, no, no.

325
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:45,000
 I'm going to read the words.

326
00:26:45,000 --> 00:27:02,000
 It says, turn your eyes upon Jesus, look full in his wonderful face, and the things of earth will grow strangely dim in the light of his glory and grace.

327
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:04,000
 I'm going to read it again.

328
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:24,000
 Turn your eyes upon Jesus, look full in his wonderful face, and the things of earth will grow strangely dim in the light of his glory and grace.

329
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:46,000
 If we can all just close our eyes for a second.

330
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:52,000
 Lord, help us to fix our eyes on you.

331
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:57,000
 To turn our eyes to you for all of our needs.

332
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:08,000
 To look to you as our source of strength and peace, our guide, our help in times of trouble, but also in times of blessing.

333
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:13,000
 That we will not forget that you are the main character.

334
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:18,000
 That our lives are about you and bringing you glory.

335
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:31,000
 And that when we start to look up to God, instead of looking ahead on earth, the things that aren't important to God really do fade away.

336
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:40,000
 Our fleshly desires, our pride, our selfish ways, and we start to love God more and love his people.

337
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:44,000
 It's all about you, Lord.

338
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:52,000
 In our finances, we ask that you would help to steward what you have given us.

339
00:28:52,000 --> 00:29:04,000
 In our homes, Lord, we would ask how we can honour you with our children, with our spouses and relatives.

340
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:15,000
 In our workplaces, we would ask how we can glorify you in our behaviour towards our colleagues and our bosses.

341
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 In our serving, Lord, we would humble ourselves and see our giftings as a way to build up your church body and praise you.

342
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 On our commute to work, Lord, we would ask how can I show God's love?

343
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 Giving up my seat, perhaps? Very rare.

344
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 There are so many areas of our lives that we need your help, God.

345
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:52,000
 We don't want to be the main character, Lord.

346
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 That's your job.

347
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,000
 And Lord, help us to do it joyfully.

348
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:02,000
 Lord, there is joy in serving you.

349
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 There is joy in giving our lives to you, Lord.

350
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,000
 Let's just take a moment.

351
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:24,000
 If anything is coming up, if God is pointing out anything that you may need to repent of, you can do that now.

352
